name: Algorithms
image_alt: A diagram showing the algorithm for Euclid's algorithm.
description: This is a fundamental class for any CS student to take, teaching more advanced algorithmic concepts like graph algorithms and dynamic programming.

name: Data Structures
image_alt: A diagram of different types of data structures.
description: This class taught us more advanced data structures, like red-black trees and different kinds of efficient automata.

name: Operating Systems
image_alt: A collage of popular operating systems.
description: This class was all about operating systems, going into things like synchronization, virtual memory, and multiprocessing. We also developed most of an OS for this class.

name: Software Engineering
image_alt: A diagram showing the Agile development cycle.
description: This class went through the process of software engineering, teaching us different SWE concepts like Agile, all while we worked in groups of 10+ people developing a project.

name: Web Development
image_alt: A diagram showing how client HTTP Requests get handled by servers, which then respond with an HTTP Response packet.
description: Hello whoever's grading this! In this class, we learned the fundamentals of web development and developed our own portfolio site.

name: Real Analysis
image_alt: An image of a graph and an integral, showing the basics of Riemann integration.
description: This class was about real analysis, and over the three courses in the series it spanned a massive amount of knowledge (going through effectively all of 'Little Rudin', as the textbook is affectionately known)
